The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Subhas put on ventilator
                                                                                                               Subhas put on ventilator
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, Aug. 2: State transport minister Subhas Chakraborty has been put on a ventilator with his condition deteriorating since last night.        
	Chakrabortys condition remains critical and last night he was put on ventilator. He was also requiring drugs to maintain his blood pressure, said a medical bulletin issued by the private hospital where he is admitted.        
	Doctors said Chakrabortys blood pressure and heart rate were fluctuating, and that he had a platelet transfusion this evening. The six-member medical board has decided that he should undergo dialysis from tonight.        
	Doctors said his white blood cell (WBC) count had increased to 1,600 from yesterdays figure of 1,000. However, the other parameters have deteriorated, causing worry, a doctor said.        
	Today, industries minister Nirupam Sen and Left Front chairman Biman Bose visited him in AMRI Hospital in Salt Lake.        
	The minister was admitted to hospital on July 27 with a chest infection and other complications. Shyam Agarwal, a senior physician from Gangaram Hospital, New Delhi, visited him last night and this morning. Senior haematologists and lung specialists visited him yesterday.                                                                                                                                                                           
